### Week 5 — Realtime + Chat Polish

**Files created:**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/lib/supabase/realtime.ts` | Supabase Realtime subscription helpers |
| `src/components/chat/ChatMessageList.tsx` | Virtualized message list for performance |
| `src/lib/hooks/useChatSubscription.ts` | Hook: subscribe to new messages in real-time |
| `src/lib/hooks/useInsightSubscription.ts` | Hook: subscribe to new insights pushed to chat |

**Realtime setup**: Subscribe to `chat_messages` table filtered by `business_id`. When another team member logs a transaction, the chat updates in real-time for all connected users.

**Testing checkpoint — Phase 2 done when:**
- [ ] User types "I bought 100 bottles of shampoo lavender small for ₦50 each" → AI returns structured confirmation card
- [ ] Tapping Confirm writes transaction + updates stock level
- [ ] Tapping Cancel does nothing to DB
- [ ] Chat history persists across page reloads
- [ ] Conversation history sidebar shows grouped sessions
- [ ] Quick action pills work (pre-fill the input)
- [ ] Streaming works — text appears word by word
- [ ] Corrections work — "no, it was 200 units" updates the card
- [ ] Realtime — second browser tab sees messages appear
- [ ] Error states display for API failures

**Common failure points:**
- Claude returns conversational text instead of JSON — fix: enforce JSON in system prompt with `"You MUST respond with ONLY a JSON object"` and use `response_format` if available
- Supabase Realtime not firing — fix: ensure the table has `REPLICA IDENTITY FULL` set and the Realtime publication includes the table
- Stock going negative — fix: `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` + check in transaction
- Token limit exceeded — fix: conversation history truncation (keep system prompt + last 20 messages + current message, summarize older context)
